JOHANNESBURG-The Public Servants Association has also added its voice to concerns that schools opened prematurely. Several schools around the country had to close their doors after teachers and pupils tested positive for COVID-19. For more we're joined by Basic Education Spokesperson Elijah Mhlanga. JOHANNESBURG - The Public Servants Association has also added its voice to concerns that schools opened prematurely. Several schools around the country had to close their doors after teachers and pupils tested positive for COVID-19. READ: COVID-19: Cosas threatens to shutdown schools However, Basic Education spokesperson Elijah Mhlanga believes schools should remain open, which is consistent with President Cyril Ramaphosa's announcement for more sectors to open. " You can't send adults to work and keep expanding sectors to go back to work and you say the kids must stay at home. It doesn't make sense". - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.